'''Plantin'''是一款旧式衬线字体，以十六世纪出版商[[克里斯托夫·普朗坦|克里斯托夫·普朗坦]]命名<ref name="History of the Monotype Corporation">{{cite book|last1=Slinn|first1=Judy|last2=Carter|first2=Sebastian|last3=Southall|first3=Richard|author-link2=Sebastian Carter|title=History of the Monotype Corporation|pages=202–3 etc.}}</ref>。这款字是英国[[蒙納公司|蒙納公司]]为其自动铸排机系统设计制作，原型可追溯到十六岁世纪刻字师[[罗贝尔·格朗容|罗贝尔·格朗容]]刻制、并保存于[[安特卫普|安特卫普]][[普朗坦-莫雷图斯博物馆|普朗坦-莫雷图斯博物馆]]的Gros Cicero活字。<ref>{{cite web
 |url          = http://brigitteschuster.com/media/documents/MonotypePlantin-AdigitalRevival.pdf
 |title        = Monotype Plantin: A Digital Revival by Brigitte Schuster
 |last         = Schuster
 |first        = Brigitte
 |date         = 2010
 |publisher    = [[Royal_Academy_of_Art,_The_Hague|Royal Academy of Art, The Hague]] (M.A. thesis)
 |accessdate   = 23 May 2014
 |archive-date = 2016-02-18
 |archive-url  = https://web.archive.org/web/20160218145213/http://brigitteschuster.com/media/documents/MonotypePlantin-AdigitalRevival.pdf
}}</ref>

蒙纳公司当时制作这款字的目的在于他们需要一款更粗的字形以适用于光面纸张的印刷<ref name="20c">{{citation
 | last = Carter | first = Sebastian
 | pages = 28–29
 | publisher = W. W. Norton & Company
 | title = Twentieth Century Type Designers
 | year = 1995}}.</ref> 在设计构思时，蒙纳公司的工程部经理[[弗兰克·辛曼·皮尔蓬特|弗兰克·辛曼·皮尔蓬特]]特地到安特卫普的普朗坦-莫雷图斯博物馆拿到了一些字体样张<ref name="morison">{{cite book|last1=Morison|first1=Stanley|title=A Tally of Types|url=https://archive.org/details/tallyoftypes0000mori|url-access=registration|date=7 June 1973|publisher=CUP Archive|isbn=978-0-521-09786-4|pages=[https://archive.org/details/tallyoftypes0000mori/page/22 22]–24}}</ref>。这款字也是蒙纳公司第一批不是单纯复制英国流行的印刷字体而进行传统复刻的字体之一，自发布之后广受欢迎，让蒙纳公司之后的二三十年加速了对其他经典字体的复刻。Plantin也是三十年代制作[[Times_New_Roman|Times New Roman]]字体时的参照字体之一。<ref name="History of the Monotype Corporation" /><ref>{{citation
 | last1 = Meggs | first1 = Philip B.
 | last2 = Carter | first2 = Rob
 | contribution = 29. Plantin
 | isbn = 978-0-471-28429-1
 | pages = 302–311
 | publisher = John Wiley and Sons
 | title = Typographic Specimens: The Great Typefaces
 | year = 1993}}.</ref> Plantin字体家族包括常规体、细体、粗体以及配套的意大利体。

==设计灵感==
[[File:Plantin-Moretus_punches_1.jpg|thumb]], the masters used to stamp [[Matrix_(printing)|matrices]] used to cast metal type, at the [[Plantin-Moretus_Museum|Plantin-Moretus Museum]]. Its unique collection of original sixteenth-century matrices and punches inspired the Plantin design.]]
[[File:Antwerp_Belgium_Museum-Plantin-Moretus-05.jpg|thumb]]的普朗坦-莫雷图斯博物馆]]

建于1876年的普朗坦-莫雷图斯博物馆保留了普朗坦、莫雷图斯等人的大量收藏，其中包括十六世纪最著名的字体，吸引了弗兰克·辛曼·皮尔蓬特前往拜访。 <ref name="The materials of typefounding">{{cite web|last1=Mosley|first1=James|title=The materials of typefounding|url=http://typefoundry.blogspot.co.uk/2006/01/materials-of-typefounding.html|website=Type Foundry|accessdate=14 August 2015|archive-date=2015-08-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150828050841/http://www.typefoundry.blogspot.co.uk/2006/01/materials-of-typefounding.html}}</ref>弗兰克·辛曼·皮尔蓬特所参照的Gros Cicero的字，是十七世纪初普朗坦-莫雷图斯印刷所使用字体之一，由罗贝尔·格朗容设计。<ref name="20c"/><ref name="morison"/><ref name="Where Did Times New Roman Come From?">{{cite web|last1=Mann|first1=Meredith|title=Where Did Times New Roman Come From?|url=http://www.nypl.org/blog/2014/12/09/times-new-roman|publisher=[[New_York_Public_Library|New York Public Library]]|accessdate=2 February 2016|archive-date=2021-03-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210314084645/https://www.nypl.org/blog/2014/12/09/times-new-roman}}</ref><ref name="Vervliet2008">{{cite book|author=Hendrik D. L. Vervliet|title=The Palaeotypography of the French Renaissance: Selected Papers on Sixteenth-century Typefaces|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=6sidSDlif48C&pg=PA226|year=2008|publisher=BRILL|isbn=978-90-04-16982-1|pages=226–7}}</ref>)

Plantin的金属铸造活字由蒙纳公司萨利工厂制作，由弗兰克·辛曼·皮尔蓬特和Fritz Stelzer主持。选择这样一款法国文艺复兴时期的活字在当时并不常见，因为当时英国印刷商喜欢用[[Caslon|Caslon]]或者[[尼古拉·詹森|尼古拉·詹森]]十五世纪设计的复刻字体。尽管如此，在其后的几十年里，多家铸排机厂商都复刻了多款Aldine或法国文艺复兴时期的字体，其中包括蒙纳自家的[[Poliphilus_(typeface)|Poliphilus]]、[[Bembo|Bembo]] 和[[Garamond|Garamond]]，还有莱诺的 [[Granjon_(typeface)|Granjon]] 、[[George_W._Jones_(printer)|Estienne]] 等等，都是很受欢迎的正文字体。

==设计==
[[File:Old_Style.jpg|thumb]], a delicate reinterpretation of pre nineteenth-century printing styles that became popular in the late nineteenth century. While offering a version of it as one of their first faces, Monotype in creating Plantin aimed to offer a more solid design that would print clearly.]]
以精美印刷闻名的Claude Lamesle在其1742年样张中展示了格朗容字体原有的风貌。<ref name="Épreuves générales des caracteres">{{cite book|last1=Lamesle|first1=Claude|title=Épreuves générales des caracteres|date=1742|page=55|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4gr11pmlvgoC&printsec=frontcover}}</ref><ref name="Vervliet2008" /> Mosley has close-up images of some characters of the face.<ref name="Mosley Gros Cicero" />{{efn|A better-quality digitisation of the whole specimen is available but it does not include this leaf.<ref name="Épreuves générales des caracteres colour">{{cite book|last1=Lamesle|first1=Claude|title=Épreuves générales des caracteres|date=1742|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Fy3g7OP-VV8C&printsec=frontcover}}</ref>}}而Plantin保留了格朗容设计中高大的[[x字高|x字高]]的特点，但把[[降部|降部]]改短，并放大了小写字母a、e的字怀<ref name="morison"/>。并非所有字体都源自格朗容，因为十六世纪的法国并不使用字母J、U和W；另外在印刷字体样张时，小写字母a被替换成了一个十八世纪风格的设计。<ref name="Matthew Carter">{{cite book|last1=Mosley|first1=James|chapter=Reviving the Classics: Matthew Carter and the Interpretation of Historical Models|editor1-last=Mosley|editor1-first=James|editor2-last=Re|editor2-first=Margaret|editor3-last=Drucker|editor3-first=Johanna|editor4-last=Carter|editor4-first=Matthew|title=Typographically Speaking: The Art of Matthew Carter|date=2003|publisher=Princeton Architectural Press|isbn=9781568984278|pages=31–34|chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=WqXd_w4S4SsC&pg=PA32|quote=Plantin was a recreation of one of the old types held at the Plantin-Moretus Museum in Antwerp, of which a specimen, printed in 1905, had been acquired by Pierpont on a visit. The type from which the specimen was printed was not only centuries old and worn almost beyond use, but it was contaminated with wrong-font letters (notably the letter ‘a’) and the italic did not even belong to the roman. The revival, derived by Monotype from an indirect and confused original, is as sound a piece of type-making as was ever created in the 20th century…behind the foggy image of the roman type lies the...'Gros Cicero' Roman of [[Robert_Granjon|Robert Granjon]], acquired by the Plantin printing office after the death of its founder.|access-date=2021-02-14|archive-date=2020-11-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201105152959/https://books.google.com/books?id=WqXd_w4S4SsC&pg=PA32}}</ref><ref name="Mosley Gros Cicero">{{cite web|last1=Mosley|first1=James|title=Comments on Typophile thread|url=http://www.typophile.com/node/53050|website=Typophile (archived)|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111013140635/http://www.typophile.com/node/53050|accessdate=16 December 2016|archive-date=2011-10-13|quote=The consensus appears to be that not only the wrong-fount a in the cases at Antwerp but also the italic that Monotype adapted for their Plantin (which can be seen on that first page of the 1905 specimen) may be the work of Johann Michael Schmidt (died 1750), also known as J. M. Smit or Smid.}}</ref>



==应用及影响==
[[File:Times_ancestors.png|thumb]], [[Baskerville|Baskerville]] and Plantin. Times is most based on Plantin, but with the letters made taller and its appearance "modernised" by adding eighteenth- and nineteenth-century influences similar to Baskerville and Perpetua, in particular enhancing the stroke contrast.]]
[[File:Plantin_Fontshop.gif|thumb]], showing infant styles and the condensed "News" and "Headline" styles sold for newspapers.]]

这款字以其粗狂、扎实的设计在二十世纪早期大为流行，广泛用于商业以及报纸印刷。<ref name="Modern Publicity">{{cite journal|title=Monotype (advert)|journal=Modern Publicity|date=1930|page=187|url=http://magazines.iaddb.org/issue/MP/1930-01-01|accessdate=15 March 2017}}{{Dead link}}</ref><ref name="Twenty Years of Advertising Typography">{{cite journal|last1=Warde|first1=Beatrice|title=Twenty Years of Advertising Typography|journal=Advertiser's Weekly|date=1932|page=130|url=http://magazines.iaddb.org/issue/ADW/1932-07-28/edition/1000/page/42?query=|accessdate=15 March 2017|archive-date=2021-02-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210224092330/https://magazines.iaddb.org/issue/ADW/1932-07-28/edition/1000/page/42?query=}}</ref><ref name="Hackney">{{cite web|last1=Hackney|first1=Fiona Anne Seaton|title="They Opened Up a Whole New World": Feminine Modernity and the Feminine Imagination in Women's Magazines, 1919-1939|url=https://research.gold.ac.uk/7998/1/Redacted_History_thesis_Hackney.pdf|publisher=Goldsmith's College (PhD thesis)|accessdate=15 March 2017|archive-date=2017-03-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170316115613/https://research.gold.ac.uk/7998/1/Redacted_History_thesis_Hackney.pdf}}</ref><ref name="Lethbridge2013">{{cite book|author=Lucy Lethbridge|title=Servants: A Downstairs View of Twentieth-century Britain|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=BY7ynqJmRKsC&pg=PA187|date=14 March 2013|publisher=A&C Black|isbn=978-1-4088-3407-7|pages=187–8|access-date=2021-02-14|archive-date=2017-03-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170316130446/https://books.google.com/books?id=BY7ynqJmRKsC&pg=PA187}}</ref>}} As the basic font is relatively dark on the page, Monotype offered a 'light' version as well as a bold, which [[Hugh_Williamson_(book_designer)|Hugh Williamson]] describes as "particularly suitable for bookwork."<ref name="Methods of Book Design">{{cite book|last1=Williamson|first1=Hugh|author-link=Hugh Williamson (book designer)|title=Methods of Book Design|year=1966|url=https://archive.org/details/methodsofbookdes0000unse|publisher=Oxford University Press|page=[https://archive.org/details/methodsofbookdes0000unse/page/81 81]}}</ref>

两次世界大战之间，这款字被用于[[Francis_Meynell|Francis Meynell]]的Pelican出版社、Cloister出版社，以及[[剑桥大学出版社|剑桥大学出版社]]。<ref name="morison"/> 还有为[[Nonesuch_Press|Nonesuch Press]]出版社制作的定制版，拉高了小写字母的升部和降部。<ref name="Poetry Books for the Trala">{{cite web|last1=Steeves|first1=Andrew|title=Poetry Books for the Trala|date=14 April 2011|url=http://gaspereaupress.blogspot.co.uk/2011/04/poetry-books-for-trala.html|publisher=Gaspereau Press|accessdate=12 March 2017|archive-date=2018-03-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180310010235/http://gaspereaupress.blogspot.co.uk/2011/04/poetry-books-for-trala.html}}</ref> 蒙纳公司还在七十年代为《[[观察家报|观察家报]]》制作了窄体版的 News Plantin。<ref name="Small Print">{{cite journal|last1=Luna|first1=Paul|title=Small Print|journal=Designer|date=1986|quote=The first national to install a Lasercomp, it overcame the lack of suitable text faces by commissioning its own, a slightly condensed version of Plantin.}}</ref><ref name="History of the Monotype Corporation" /> 另外还有一款「儿童版」，小写字母a、g采用单层设计，y两边保持竖直。 

[[ABC新闻|ABC新闻]]于1978年到1999年一直采用此字体。 [[Monocle_(2007_magazine)|''Monocle'']]杂志全线也采用Plantin和 [[Helvetica|Helvetica]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://fontfeed.com/archives/in-use-plantin-for-monocle |first=Stephen |last=Coles |title=In Use: Plantin for Monocle |date=February 13, 2009 |accessdate=2009-12-23 |publisher=[[FSI_FontShop_International|FSI FontShop International]] |work=The FontFeed |archive-date=2009-08-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090827081224/http://fontfeed.com/archives/in-use-plantin-for-monocle/ }}</ref>

Plantin也是蒙纳公司最著名的Times New Roman字体的设计基础。<ref name="Time and Times again">{{cite web|last1=Rhatigan|first1=Dan|title=Time and Times again|url=http://ultrasparky.org/archives/2011/09/time_and_times_.html|publisher=Monotype|accessdate=28 July 2015|archive-date=2018-10-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181019041116/http://ultrasparky.org/archives/2011/09/time_and_times_.html}}</ref><ref name="Hutt Times Roman: a re-assessment">{{cite journal|last1=Hutt|first1=Allen|title=Times Roman: a re-assessment|journal=Journal of Typographic Research|date=1970|volume=4|issue=3|pages=259–270|url=http://visiblelanguagejournal.com/issue/15|accessdate=5 March 2017|archive-date=2017-03-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170305192327/http://visiblelanguagejournal.com/issue/15}}</ref> Times与Plantin非常类似，但通过增加笔画对比显得更现代、更锋利。<ref name="Anatomy of a Typeface">{{cite book|last1=Lawson|first1=Alexander|title=Anatomy of a Typeface|date=1990|publisher=David R. Godine|location=New York|isbn=9780879233334|pages=270–294|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=FiJ87ixLs0sC&pg=PA270|accessdate=6 March 2016}}</ref><ref name="Changing the Times">{{cite web|last1=Morison|first1=Stanley|title=Changing the Times|url=http://www.eyemagazine.com/feature/article/stanley-morison-changing-the-times|website=Eye|accessdate=28 July 2015|archive-date=2018-10-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181014064523/http://www.eyemagazine.com/feature/article/stanley-morison-changing-the-times}}</ref><ref name="Haley1992">{{cite book|author=Allan Haley|title=Typographic Milestones|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dKeVor1olhkC&pg=PA106|date=15 September 1992|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|isbn=978-0-471-28894-7|page=106}}</ref> Allan Haley commented that Times New Roman "looks like Plantin on a diet."<ref name="ABC's of type">{{cite book |last1=Haley |first1=Allen |title=ABC's of type |date=1990 |publisher=Watson-Guptill Publications |isbn=9780823000531 |page=[https://archive.org/details/abcsoftype0000hale/page/86 86] |url=https://archive.org/details/abcsoftype0000hale/page/86 }}</ref>

最近其他厂商也有很多不同的数码复刻版本，其中包括Chester Jenkins和[[Kris_Sowersby|Kris Sowersby]] 设计的Galaxie Copernicusis<ref name="Heck GC review">{{cite web |last1=Heck |first1=Bethany |title=Galaxie Copernicus review |url=https://fontreviewjournal.com/galaxie-copernicus/ |website=Font Review Journal |accessdate=13 September 2019 |archive-date=2021-03-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308131157/https://fontreviewjournal.com/galaxie-copernicus/ }}</ref><ref name="Eye Reputations: Kris Sowersby">{{cite web |last1=Thomson |first1=Mark |last2=Sowersby |first2=Kris |title=Reputations: Kris Sowersby |url=http://www.eyemagazine.com/feature/article/reputations-kris-sowersby |website=Eye |accessdate=12 September 2019 |archive-date=2021-02-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210225083253/http://www.eyemagazine.com/feature/article/reputations-kris-sowersby }}</ref>

